docs.abstract: The social media giant acted one day after Google, facing intense pressure from employees, made a similar decision.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Facebook said on Friday that it would no longer force employees to settle sexual harassment claims in private arbitration, making it the latest technology company to do away with a practice that critics say has stacked the deck against victims of harassment.

headline.main: Facebook to Drop Forced Arbitration in Harassment Cases
headline.print_headline: Facebook to Drop Forced Arbitration in Sexual Harassment Cases
